  <recipe id="Thumbprints">
    <head>
      <title>Thumbprints</title>
      <source>Marsha</source>
      <categories>
        <cat class="main">Cookies</cat>
        <cat class="region">America</cat>
      </categories>
    </head>
    <description>This is a classic recipe that my mom and I have tweaked over the years. We don't love the jelly version that most people know of, preferring instead to use candied cherries or other fruit. I also love using Nutella, marzipan or caramel but know that some regard these fillings as gilding an already lovely lily.</description>
    <ingredients system="US">
      <ing-div>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1/4</qty>
            <unit>cup</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>packed brown sugar</item>
<!--1/4 cup packed brown sugar-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1/4</qty>
            <unit>cup</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>shortening</item>
<!--1/4 cup shortening-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <alt-ing>
            <amt>
              <qty>1/4</qty>
              <unit>cup</unit>
            </amt>
            <item>butter</item>
<!--1/4 cup butter-->
          </alt-ing>
          <alt-ing>
            <item>margarine</item>
            <prep>softened</prep>
<!--margarine, softened-->
          </alt-ing>
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1/2</qty>
            <unit>teaspoon</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>vanilla</item>
<!--1/2 teaspoon vanilla-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1</qty>
          </amt>
          <item>egg</item>
          <prep>separated</prep>
<!--1 egg, separated-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1</qty>
            <unit>cup</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>all-purpose flour</item>
<!--1 cup all-purpose flour-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1/4</qty>
            <unit>teaspoon</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>salt</item>
<!--1/4 teaspoon salt-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>3/4</qty>
            <unit>cup</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>finely chopped walnuts</item>
<!--3/4 cup finely chopped walnuts-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>15</qty>
          </amt>
          <item>red candied cherries</item>
          <prep>each cut in half</prep>
<!--15 red candied cherries, each cut in half-->
        </ing>
      </ing-div>
    </ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>Heat oven to <temp><qty>350</qty><tempunit unit="F" system="US">degrees</tempunit><!--350  degrees--></temp>.</step>
      <step>Mix brown sugar, shortening, butter, vanilla and egg yolk in medium bowl. Stir in flour and salt until dough holds together (dough will be very soft). Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Beat egg white slightly. Dip each ball into egg white. Roll in nuts. Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Press a candied cherry half into the center of each cookie.</step>
      <step>Bake about 10 minutes or until light brown (watch closely – they brown quickly!). Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack right away.</step>
      <step>(Variations: Instead of a cherry, use a thumb to make an impression in each cookie and then bake. When the cookies are cool, fill with Nutella, colored marzipan, jelly or caramel confectionary filling.) </step>
    </directions>
  </recipe>
